{"lemma":"مَظِنَّة","slug":"مَظِنَّة","root":"ظ.ن.ن","root_slug":"ظ-ن-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ن-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27706"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B8%D9%90%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27706","headword_ar":"مَظِنَّةٌ","root":"Zn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, Msb, TA,) of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZan~apN","text_ar":"مَظَنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Ibn-Málik and others, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZan~apN","text_ar":"مِظَنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", are dial. vars., (TA,) or [rather]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZin~apu $aYo'K","text_ar":"مَظِنَّةُ شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IF, S, Msb, K, TA,) signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, S, Msb, K, TA,) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accustomed place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, S, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is thought to be the existence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, S, Msb, K, TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where a thing is thought to be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or it signifies, (Mgh, Msb,) or signifies also, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place where a thing is known to be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person, in which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in whom, a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, is thought, supposed, presumed, suspected, inferred, known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accustomed, to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exist:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] accord. to IAth, by rule it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZan~apN","text_ar":"مَظَنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [it may therefore be properly rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of thinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the existence"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZin~apN lika*aA","text_ar":"مَظِنَّةٌ لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be well expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person, that occasions one's thinking, supposing, presuming suspecting, inferring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing, the existence of such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, in it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an indication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a symptom, diagnostic, characteristic, sign, mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"token, of the existence of such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZaAn~u","text_ar":"مَظَانُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, Mgh, Msb, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoDiEu","text_ar":"مَوْضِعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA maZin~apN mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"كَذَا مَظِنَّةٌ مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a place is a place in which such a one is known"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN maZin~apN mino ka*aA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مَظِنَّةٌ مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is one in whom such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, is known"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN maZin~apN liloxayori","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مَظِنَّةٌ لِلْخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is one in whom good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness, is thought"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 437.) And En-Nábighah says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faA_ino yaku EaAmirN qado qaAla jaholFA\n                      \n                     \n                        faA_in~a maZin~apa Aljaholi Al$~abaAbu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if 'Ámir has spoken ignorantly, verily youthfulness is a state in which ignorance is usually found to exist"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb: *) or, as some relate the verse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ibaAbu","text_ar":"السِّبَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mutual reviling is an act in which"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (S:) or, accord. to another relation, the latter hemistich is"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faA_in~a maTiy~apa Aljaholi Al$~abaAbu"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1926},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA;) because one finds it [i. e. youthfulness] to be easy like as he does the beast on which one rides. (TA.) And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talabahu maZaAn~ahu","text_ar":"طَلَبَهُ مَظَانَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in the places where he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was thought to be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by night and by day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamaZin~apN A^ano","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمَظِنَّةٌ اَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEala *`lika","text_ar":"يَفْعَلَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is apt, meet, fitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suited, for one to think of his doing that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner one says of two, and of a pl. number, and of a female. (Lh, M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Mgh","Msb","TA","IF","S","K"]}]}}